msgid ""
"How did plastic garbage patches floating in the ocean become an object of publ"
"ic concern? Baptiste Monsaingeon relates the media campaigns that turned the g"
"radual accumulation of oceanic waste from an abstract and imperceptible concer"
"n to a dire emergency requiring immediate attention."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In the next few decades only strong and effective countermeasures will be able"
" to halt the advance of this process. We propose for your consideration the id"
"ea that global spending on armaments should be re-directed (along with other m"
"easures) to address social and environmental deterioration in a more focused m"
"anner than at present."
msgstr "En las próximas décadas sólo se podrá parar el avance de este proceso mediante contramedidas fuertes y eficaces. Proponemos para su consideración la idea de que el gasto global en armamento sea redirigido (junto con otras medidas) a abordar el deterioro social y medioambiental de una manera más concentrada que en el presente."

msgid ""
"It is the accepted practice all round the globe that the military is called in"
" to assist those affected by sudden and unexpected environmental disasters. It"
" would simply be a logical extension of this to employ such a resource in coun"
"teracting the effects of large-scale and inexorably-advancing catastrophes."
msgstr ""

